================================================================================
                      PIN RECOMMENDATIONS
================================================================================

Current Assignment: OPTIMAL

Recommendations:
  1. Keep current pin assignments - they follow BGA standard layout
  2. Ensure proper PCB trace lengths from FPGA to connectors
  3. Add series resistors on LED outputs for ESD protection
  4. Consider adding RC debounce on reset input
  5. Route VSS planes continuously under and around device
  6. Keep VDD/VSS vias within 2.5cm of respective pads

Alternative Pin Assignments:
  - Clock could use H2, H1 (still on Bank 1)
  - Reset could use H5, H6 (still on Bank 1)
  - LEDs could use adjacent pins (G15, G18, etc.)

Recommended PCB Layout:
  - Place FPGA in center of board
  - Route power planes on inner layers
  - Place decoupling capacitors within 1cm of device
  - Keep clock signal short and away from signal returns

